âœ… P2: NumPy Operations
(a) Remove Non-Numeric Values

Sure-Shot Theory:

NumPy is a numerical computing library that supports fast array operations.
Non-numeric values can be removed using boolean indexing and vectorized operations without using loops.
This improves performance and efficiency in data processing.

(b) Checkerboard Matrix

Sure-Shot Theory:

NumPy slicing allows efficient creation of patterned matrices.
A checkerboard pattern is created by assigning values to alternate rows and columns using slicing techniques.

ðŸ”¹ Aim 1: Remove Non-Numeric Values from Array

import numpy as np

arr = np.array(['10', '20', 'abc', '30', 'xyz'])

numeric = arr[np.char.isnumeric(arr)]
numeric = numeric.astype(int)

print(numeric)

ðŸ”¹ Aim 2: 8Ã—8 Checkerboard Pattern

import numpy as np

board = np.zeros((8, 8), dtype=int)

board[1::2, ::2] = 1
board[::2, 1::2] = 1

print(board

import numpy as np

a = np.array(['10','20','x'])
print(a[np.char.isnumeric(a)].astype(int))

b = np.zeros((8,8),int)
b[1::2,::2]=1
b[::2,1::2]=1
print(b)


